claim.claim-text:
1. A non-transitory processor readable storage medium having a plurality of instructions stored thereon that when executed by a processor, cause the processor to perform operations comprising:
receiving, at a server computing device, a first signal, the first signal being received from a first mobile computing device and indicative of a first state change, the first state change occurring at the first mobile computing device;
receiving, at the server computing device, a second signal, the second signal being received from a second mobile computing device and indicative of a second state change, the second stage change occurring at the second mobile computing device;
determining, at the server computing device, that the first state change and the second state change are related, wherein determining that the first state change and the second state change are related is based at least in part on the first mobile computing device and the second mobile computing device being located at a common geographic location and an amount of time between the first state change and the second state change;
determining, at the server computing device, that a third mobile computing device is currently located at the common geographic location; and
transmitting, by the server computing device, to the third mobile computing device, a third signal indicative of a recommended state change to the third mobile computing device, the recommended state change being based at least in part on of the first state change and the second state change.

10. A computer-implemented method comprising:
receiving, at a server computing device, a first signal, the first signal being received from a first mobile computing device and indicative of a first state change, the first change occurring at the first mobile computing device;
receiving, at the server computing device, a second signal, the second signal being received from a second mobile computing device and indicative of a second state change, the second state change occurring at the second mobile computing device;
determining, at the server computing device, that the first state change and the second state change are related, wherein determining that the first state change and the second state change are related is based at least in part on a confidence threshold calculation, the confidence threshold calculation being based at least in part on (i) a current location of the first mobile computing device and a current location of the second mobile computing device being a common geographic location, and (ii) a percentage of devices currently located at the common geographic location having undergone the first state change or the second state change;
determining, at the server computing device, that a third mobile computing device is currently located at the common geographic location; and
transmitting, by the server computing device, to the third mobile computing device, a third signal, the third signal indicative of a recommended state change to the third mobile computing device, the recommended state change being based at least in part on of the first state change and the second state change.

16. A computing system comprising:
one or more processors configured to:
receive, at a server computing device, a first signal, the first signal being received from a first mobile computing device and indicative of a first state change, the first change occurring at the first mobile computing device;
receive, at the server computing device, a second signal, the second signal being received from a second mobile computing device and indicative of a second state change, the second state change occurring at the second mobile computing device;
determine, at the server computing device, that the first state change and the second state change are related, wherein determining that the first state change and the second state change are related is based at least in part on a confidence threshold calculation, the confidence threshold calculation being based at least in part on (i) a current location of the first mobile computing device and a current location of the second mobile computing device being a common geographic location, and (ii) a percentage of devices currently located at the common geographic location having undergone the first state change or the second state change
determine, at the server computing device, that a third mobile computing device is currently located at the common geographic location;
determine, at the server computing device, a type of the third signal, the type being one or more of a push notification and an alert; and
transmit, by the server computing device, to the third mobile computing device, a third signal, the third signal indicative of a recommended state change to the third mobile computing device, the recommended state change being based at least in part on of the first state change and the second state change.
